T funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using the premium index methodology. The funding rate is determined by the 8-hour time-weighted average premium between the perpetual contract price and the underlying spot index. Portfolio margin mode allows cross-collateralization with other positions, reducing capital requirements for delta-neutral funding strategies. Funding payments are exchanged directly between long and short position holders without affecting OKX's revenue."}]]}],"$L3",["$L4","$L5","$L6"],"$L7"]}],"$L8"]}]]}],["$L9","$La"],"$Lb"]}],"loading":null,"isPartial":false}
3:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","FET","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FET represents Fetch.ai's artificial intelligence protocol, making it sensitive to AI sector sentiment and resulting in volatile funding rates. The token's mid-tier volume on OKX creates opportunities for funding rate mispricing, especially during AI-related market events. OKX's robust API infrastructure supports automated monitoring of FET funding rate changes for systematic arbitrage strategies."}]]}]
4:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical FET Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FET/USDT funding rates on OKX have shown strong correlation with broader AI sector momentum and Fetch.ai development announcements. During Q3 2024, funding rates ranged from -0.15% to +0.45% per 8-hour period, with persistent positive funding during AI market rallies. The pair exhibits higher funding rate volatility compared to major cryptocurrencies, creating more frequent arbitrage windows. Weekend periods often show reduced funding premiums as institutional activity decreases."}]]}]
5:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Portfolio Margin Arbitrage Advantages"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"OKX's portfolio margin system calculates risk across all positions, enabling efficient capital utilization for FET funding strategies. Traders can hedge FET perpetual positions using correlated AI tokens or maintain spot FET holdings as collateral while shorting perpetuals. The unified margin approach reduces the capital required for delta-neutral strategies by up to 60% compared to isolated margin. Cross-margining with stablecoin positions provides additional flexibility for managing funding payments."}]]}]
6:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management for FET Arbitrage"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FET's relatively lower liquidity compared to major cryptocurrencies increases slippage risk during position entry and exit. Market volatility around AI sector developments can cause rapid funding rate changes, potentially invalidating arbitrage setups. Auto-deleveraging risk exists during extreme market conditions, though OKX's risk management typically affects highly leveraged positions first. Traders should monitor Fetch.ai's development milestones and partnership announcements that can trigger sudden price movements affecting funding rate calculations."}]]}]
7:["$","$Lc",null,{"items":[{"question":"How does OKX calculate FET/USDT funding rates?","answer":"OKX uses the 8-hour time-weighted average premium between FET perpetual and spot prices. The calculation considers the interest rate component (typically 0.01% per 8 hours) and the premium component based on actual trading data from the FET/USDT markets."},{"question":"What are typical FET funding rate ranges on OKX?","answer":"FET funding rates typically range from -0.10% to +0.30% per 8-hour period during normal market conditions. During AI sector rallies or major Fetch.ai announcements, rates can spike to +0.50% or higher as long demand increases significantly."},{"question":"Can I use portfolio margin for FET funding strategies?","answer":"Yes, OKX's portfolio margin mode allows cross-collateralization of FET positions with other assets in your portfolio. This reduces capital requirements and enables more sophisticated hedging strategies using correlated AI tokens or major cryptocurrencies as collateral."},{"question":"What liquidity considerations affect FET arbitrage on OKX?","answer":"FET/USDT has moderate liquidity on OKX with typical spreads of 0.02-0.05%. During volatile periods or off-peak hours, spreads may widen to 0.10% or more. Large arbitrage positions should be sized considering the 24-hour volume to minimize market impact and slippage costs."}]}]
